      "content": "It's just that there's no \"navigating\" a decline, you know? You can't navigate a sunset. You just sit there and wait for the light to go out. I used to be a person who did things, who had an impact... now I'm just a burden on the system and my family. It feels like I've lost all my agency. I'm just waiting for nature to decide when I'm done, but it's taking its sweet time.",
